This is supported by the results of a recent survey carried out by the Centre for Research and Policy Making, which showed that 67 percent of females in Macedonia value abortion more than birth control.

Around two months ago, 15-year-old Alexandra Bibova from the southern town of Gevgelija had miscarried her baby after 20 weeks, allegedly after a bungled abortion procedure at a local private clinic which infected her with tetanus.

Bibova’s 19-year-old single mother claims she was raped when she was 15 but never reported it to the police. She told the media that she has dedicated her entire life to her unmarried teenage daughter and regrets very much that she didn’t take into account the risks of having an “abortion pill” in their own home two times. She reportedly pressed her older sister to abort because her family couldn’t afford to feed another child. “I lost my firstborn because abortion is not a joke and I’m afraid we will lose Alexandra too. Let other women read this and think twice before resorting to abortion,” the devastated mother said.
